<h3><a name="loading">LOADING THE DISTRIBUTION</a></h3>

Code is distributed by <i>ftp</i> in tar format or on CD-ROM in
ISO-9660 format. The distribution takes about 180 Mb of disk space
but includes libraries and executables for several different systems. Only
about 20Mb is necessary for a single operating system. To load
SPIDER use the following commands: 
d29 5
a33 6
<blockquote>
   <dl>
   <dt><kbd>cd PARENT-DIR</kbd></dt>

   <dd><kbd>(where PARENT-DIR is parent of desired location of
    SPIDER)</kbd></dd>
d35 3
a37 1
   <dt><kbd><i>mkdir spider</i></kbd></dt>
d39 3
a41 2
   <dd><kbd>(creates a new sub-directory for SPIDER, hereafter
    referred to as SPIDER_DIR)</kbd></dd>
a42 1
   <dt><kbd>From <i>ftp</i> delivery:</kbd></dt>
d44 2
a45 5
   <dd>
   <dl>
   <dt><kbd><i>tar xvf "ftp_filename" spider</i></kbd></dt>
   </dl>
   </dd>
d47 2
a48 1
   <dt><kbd>From CDROM:</kbd></dt>
d50 3
a52 8
   <dd>
   <dl>
   <dt><kbd><i>cp -r "your_cdrom_device"/spider/*
   spider</i></kbd></dt>
   </dl>
   </dd>
   </dl>
</blockquote>
d54 2
a55 1
<p>The following directories will be created:
